HEADWORD: Mesonephros
<hw>Mes`o*neph"ros</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>me`sos</grk> middle + <grk>nefro`s</grk> kidney.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The middle one of the three pairs of embryonic
renal organs developed in most vertebrates; the Wolffian body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

